      "copyright": "",
      "summary": "Patients with myalgic encephalomyelitis/chronic fatigue syndrome (ME/CFS) typically perform worse on cognitive tasks compared to controls. The present study explored the independent associations of fatigue and pain symptoms with cognitive performance in a large sample of patients who met CDC criteria of CFS (n&#xa0;=&#xa0;1375), of whom most also met NICE/ IOM criteria (n&#xa0;=&#xa0;1072). Moreover, we tested the hypothesis that these associations become stronger with older age and longer symptom duration.",
